   - **Digit Frequency Condition**: For a number to be special, each digit `k` in the number must appear exactly `k` times. This means the total length of the number must be the sum of the distinct digits in the set (since each digit `k` contributes `k` to the length).
   - **Even/Odd Length Handling**: 
     - For even-length palindromes, every digit must appear an even number of times (so that they can be split equally on both sides of the palindrome).
     - For odd-length palindromes, exactly one digit must appear an odd number of times (this digit will be the center of the palindrome).

